cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use adaptiSeq in your research, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "adaptiSeq: a self-tuning batch downloader for public sequencing data"
abstract: >-
  adaptiSeq is an importable Python tool for fetching public sequencing data and
  metadata from GSA, SRA, ENA, DDBJ, and GEO. It provides a segmented, resumable
  transfer engine, parallel metadata resolution, an adaptive batch-concurrency
  controller, and adaptive parallel Aspera.
type: software
authors:
